.:: Puzzle 6x4-Level-2-2::.
There 4 different types of food: pomegranate, avocado, plum, artichoke
The people have 4 different hobbies: chess, filmmaking, skydiving, writing
City: new-york, nizza, boston, rome
The people prefer 4 different types of sport: water-polo, baseball, rowing, badminton
House: art-deco, farmhouse, gothic-revival, modern
The people use 4 different means of transport: bike, bus, ship, train
 1. the farmhouse house is between the person who's hobby is skydiving and the person driving the bike##2
 2. the modern house is on the left of the person traveling to boston##1
 3. the person who's hobby is writing is on the left of the art-deco house##1
 4. the farmhouse house is between the person eating pomegranate and the person driving the ship##2
 5. the person who's sport is water-polo is the person eating avocado##1
 6. the person who's sport is rowing is on the far right##1
 7. the person who's hobby is filmmaking is on the right of the person who's sport is baseball##1
 8. the person driving the ship is between the person traveling to new-york and the person who's hobby is writing##2
 9. the person traveling to nizza is the person who's hobby is writing##1
10. the person who's hobby is chess is on the far left##1
11. the person who's sport is water-polo is the person traveling to boston##1
12. the person eating plum is on the left of the person who's hobby is filmmaking##1
13. the gothic-revival house is on the right of the person driving the bus##1
14. the person eating avocado is on the left of the farmhouse house##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1     |      2      |     3      |      4      |
| Food      | artichoke    | avocado       | plum   | pomegranate |
| Hobby         | chess     | skydiving   | writing    | filmmaking  |
| City   | new-york    | boston | nizza   | rome     |
| Sport   | badminton    | water-polo       | baseball | rowing        |
| House   | modern | gothic-revival   | farmhouse     | art-deco    |
| Transport     | bus       | ship        | train      | bike        |

